title: Woman asks 'what day is it?' when pulled from the rubble 228 hours after earthquake
description: A confused woman asked her rescuers "What day is it?" when pulled alive from the rubble of last week's earthquake after 228 hours, Turkey's state-run news agency Anadolu reported Wednesday, as another woman aged 77 was also rescued from the debris.

title: Cameroon finds suspected cases of Marburg virus, an illness similar to Ebola
description: Cameroonian authorities detected two suspected cases of Marburg disease on Monday in Olamze, a commune on the border with Equatorial Guinea, the public health delegate for the region, Robert Mathurin Bidjang, said on Tuesday.

title: New Zealand hostage pilot appears in photos with armed West Papua rebels
description: Separatist fighters in Indonesia's restive Papua region have released a series of images showing a pilot from New Zealand who was taken hostage more than a week ago.

title: Meet the animals with love lives more complicated than yours
description: Most people learn about "the birds and the bees" when they're young, but sex in the animal kingdom is not for the faint of heart.

title: No, aliens aren't here. Here's what high-altitude balloons are used for
description: A string of "unidentified objects" entered North American skies in the past few days only to be shot down by US military aircraft. And, no, the objects aren't the work of aliens. Human-made objects have been flying in the upper atmosphere for more than a century.

title: Four arrested in Florida for alleged roles in assassination of Haitian president
description: Four men have been arrested and charged in Florida in connection to the 2021 assassination of Haitian President Jovenel Moïse, federal officials in Miami-Dade announced Tuesday.
